lysis"],"metadata":{"id":"Tk2y17MLxNLN"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["# We compute statistical power to evaluate whether our current sample size\n","# is sufficient to detect a small effect (MDE) in conversion rate.\n","\n","MDE = 0.001  # 0.1%\n","alpha = 0.05  # 95% confidence level\n","\n","effect_size = sms.proportion_effectsize(Rate_A, Rate_A + MDE)\n","\n","power = sms.NormalIndPower().solve_power(\n","    effect_size=effect_size,\n","    nobs1=A_count,\n","    alpha=alpha,\n","    ratio=B_count / A_count,\n","    alternative=\"two-sided\"\n",")\n","\n","print(f\"Power = {power}\")"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"5P4zZLNpxNii","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1777900147035,"user_tz":-240,"elapsed":36,"user":{"displayName":"Ashot Movsisyan","userId":"17920601288898051134"}},"outputId":"3666ccfe-bde2-459e-f911-747af2905630"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["Power = 0.9999971223790768\n"]}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["Power ≈ 0.99999 → the experiment is extremely well-powered,\n","\n","---\n","\n","meaning we can almost certainly detect the specified effect size if it exists."],"metadata":{"id":"XWIhYVGsLq1U"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["#Bayesian"],"metadata":{"id":"K3AU26hcZ0-C"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["nclick_A = df.groupby(\"variant\")[\"conversion\"].sum().loc[\"A\"]\n","nclick_B = df.groupby(\"variant\")[\"conversion\"].sum().loc[\"B\"]\n","\n","\n","# prior (non-informative)\n","alpha_prior = 1\n","beta_prior = 1\n","# posterior parameters\n","alpha_A = nclick_A + alpha_prior\n","beta_A = beta_prior + (A_count - nclick_A)\n","\n","alpha_B = nclick_B + alpha_prior\n","beta_B = beta_prior + (B_count - nclick_B)\n"],"metadata":{"id":"yTTgcAKdtiSZ"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"code","source":["n_sim = 100000\n","\n","samples_A = np.random.beta(alpha_A, beta_A, n_sim)\n","samples_B = np.random.beta(alpha_B, beta_B, n_sim)"],"metadata":{"id":"sb9MQ3Apy9de"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"code","source":["prob_B_better = (samples_B > samples_A).mean()\n","print(f\"Probability that B is better than A: {prob_B_better:.2%}\")"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"2TO6c60DzAS1","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1777900147200,"user_tz":-240,"elapsed":3,"user":{"displayName":"Ashot Movsisyan","userId":"17920601288898051134"}},"outputId":"abd2f32d-d8f7-4938-f29d-0ba8f71a9323"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["Probability that B is better than A: 88.85%\n"]}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["#Z-Test"],"metadata":{"id":"lMbt6u5SRcV7"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["We perform a two-sample z-test to compare conversion rates between variants A and B.\n","This allows us to test whether the observed difference in proportions is statistically significant\n","under the null hypothesis that both groups have the same true conversion rate."],"metadata":{"id":"ofgZOTsARQ1n"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["**Hypothesis setup for the two-sample z-test:**\n","\n","H0 (Null Hypothesis):\n","The conversion rate of variant A is equal to the conversion rate of variant B.\n","i.e., p_A = p_B\n","\n","H1 (Alternative Hypothesis):\n","The conversion rates of variant A and variant B are different.\n","i.e., p_A ≠ p_B (two-sided test)\n","Новый раздел"],"metadata":{"id":"shWKPbA_RyK0"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["z_stat , p_value = proportions_ztest(\n","count = [nclick_B, nclick_A],\n","nobs = [B_count, A_count],\n","alternative = \"two-sided\"\n",")"],"metadata":{"id":"QnPMSK1OMPuk"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"code","source":["alpha = 0.05\n","\n","if p_value < alpha:\n","    conclusion = \"Reject H0: There is a statistically significant difference between A and B.\"\n","else:\n","    conclusion = \"Fail to reject H0: No statistically significant difference between A and B.\"\n","\n","print(\"Z-statistic:\", z_stat)\n","print(\"P-value:\", p_value)\n","print(\"Conclusion:\", conclusion)"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"atxduJwEZkTZ","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1777900147206,"user_tz":-240,"elapsed":4,"user":{"displayName":"Ashot Movsisyan","userId":"17920601288898051134"}},"outputId":"815c1042-3e75-471a-fad9-e1b59f01b8c2"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["Z-statistic: 1.2226883746838755\n","P-value: 0.22144741951269886\n","Conclusion: Fail to reject H0: No statistically significant difference between A and B.\n"]}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["We compute 95% confidence intervals for the conversion rates of both variants to quantify uncertainty and evaluate whether the observed difference is practically significant."],"metadata":{"id":"vHHZ55Md0_ak"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["ci_A = proportion_confint(nclick_A , A_count , alpha = 0.05 , method = \"normal\")\n","ci_B = proportion_confint(nclick_B , B_count , alpha = 0.05 , method = \"normal\")\n","\n","print(f\"Confidence interval for A = {ci_A}\")\n","print(f\"Confidence interval for B = {ci_B}\")"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"oREJuzlz09I4","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1777900147222,"user_tz":-240,"elapsed":15,"user":{"displayName":"Ashot Movsisyan","userId":"17920601288898051134"}},"outputId":"812750a0-63fe-4e8c-ce59-8e895ac77224"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["Confidence interval for A = (0.004597009278692163, 0.005003950817317439)\n","Confidence interval for B = (0.0047745645993395305, 0.00518853503165678)\n"]}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["#**Conclusion**:\n","\n","Although Bayesian analysis suggests an 88% probability that variant B outperforms A, the frequentist Z-test (p = 0.22) does not provide statistically significant evidence to reject the null hypothesis. Additionally, the confidence intervals for both variants heavily overlap, indicating that the observed difference in conversion rates is small and likely not statistically reliable.\n","\n","Conclusion: There is no strong evidence to support that variant B is better than A."],"metadata":{"id":"YD4xW4QSvA8z"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["#Secondary Metric: Revenue per Visitor\n"],"metadata":{"id":"aaw0YZ9LVU1b"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["zero_rate = df.groupby(\"variant\")[\"revenue\"].apply(lambda x: (x == 0).mean())\n","\n","plt.bar(zero_rate.index, zero_rate.values)\n","plt.title(\"Zero Revenue Rate by Variant\")\n","plt.ylabel(\"Share of zero revenue users\")\n","plt.show()"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/","height":452},"id":"aYS__C5w_25a","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1777900147393,"user_tz":-240,"elapsed":171,"user":{"displayName":"Ashot Movsisyan","userId":"17920601288898051134"}},"outputId":"b7c01355-2b6c-4ffd-c5fc-4968ea00851e"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":["<Figure size 640x480 with 1 Axes>"],"image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}}]},{"cell_type":"code","source":["rev = df[\"revenue\"]\n","\n","zero_share = (rev == 0).mean()\n","nonzero_share = (rev > 0).mean()\n","\n","plt.bar([\"Zero revenue\", \"Non-zero revenue\"], [zero_share, nonzero_share])\n","plt.title(\"Zero-inflation in Revenue\")\n","plt.ylabel(\"Share of users\")\n","plt.show()"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/","height":452},"id":"P4Zjoe4XC4Nr","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1777900147721,"user_tz":-240,"elapsed":327,"user":{"displayName":"Ashot Movsisyan","userId":"17920601288898051134"}},"outputId":"59663b7b-b15a-49c8-a6a1-e52d245857b9"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":["<Figure size 640x480 with 1 Axes>"],"image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["The revenue distribution is highly zero-inflated, with the vast majority of users generating zero revenue and only a small fraction contributing positive values. This indicates that revenue is driven by a small subset of users, making standard parametric assumptions invalid and motivating the use of robust or resampling-based methods."],"metadata":{"id":"fGxjiyf0B4lA"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["#Average order value (AOV)\n","buyers = df[df[\"revenue\"] > 0]\n","\n","buyers.groupby(\"variant\")[\"revenue\"].mean()"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/","height":176},"id":"goVtmr8PVWBr","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1777900147721,"user_tz":-240,"elapsed":5,"user":{"displayName":"Ashot Movsisyan","userId":"17920601288898051134"}},"outputId":"be4b3260-ef5b-49e6-bed9-2b7c5dfb7455"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[{"output_type":"execute_result","data":{"text/plain":["variant\n","A    46.824764\n","B    48.476036\n","Name: revenue, dtype: float64"],"text/html":["<div>\n","<style scoped>\n","    .dataframe tbody tr th:only-of-type {\n","        vertical-align: middle;\n","    }\n","\n","    .dataframe tbody tr th {\n","        vertical-align: top;\n","    }\n","\n","    .dataframe thead th {\n","        text-align: right;\n","    }\n","</style>\n","<table border=\"1\" class=\"dataframe\">\n","  <thead>\n","    <tr style=\"text-align: right;\">\n","      <th></th>\n","      <th>revenue</th>\n","    </tr>\n","    <tr>\n","      <th>variant</th>\n","      <th></th>\n","    </tr>\n","  </thead>\n","  <tbody>\n","    <tr>\n","      <th>A</th>\n","      <td>46.824764</td>\n","    </tr>\n","    <tr>\n","      <th>B</th>\n","      <td>48.476036</td>\n","    </tr>\n","  </tbody>\n","</table>\n","</div><br><label><b>dtype:</b> float64</label>"]},"metadata":{},"execution_count":120}]},{"cell_type":"code","source":["#Revenue only among buyers\n","rpv = df.groupby(\"variant\")[\"revenue\"].mean()\n","rpv"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:808